>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/13/01 10:35:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Qauding At Skyfire</span><hr size=1> Can someone with experience Quading at Skyfire post where and what to quad before 58 Fist of Karana?  Please!<br>
A couple of people have posted that it's possible to Qaud Kite at skyfire but not close to the zone.  Where are the flat area?  The only mobs that have less than 6000 hp are the Bottomless and Wyerns; other mobs have 7000 to 9000 hp that I barely have enough mana to dot/root.  Please do not talk about the Lumi Staff, most people do not have that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/13/01 11:14:03 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Qauding At Skyfire</span><hr size=1> Depends on your level. But there are flat areas on both the left wall and the right wall. Higher level being left wall. And there is a nice one right at zone in portal.<br>
<br>
No one said it was easy and it will require medding while quadding and/or a lum staff or both. It is doable and good exps but it is also easier to root/dot too. <p><p><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaktariplainsrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daktari Plainsrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://home1.gte.net/chiefq/icon1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/13/01 12:16:01 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/chiefq/cop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quading At Skyfire</span><hr size=1> I have quadded a few, and it is possible, but not worth the time IMHO.  Why you might ask?<br>
<br>
I have found that sometimes, no matter where you are, the terrain will have that one little glitch that will prevent you from casting on your quad that extra second, which leads to getting hit.<br>
<br>
The lowest HP mobs, the spermies, will hit you every once in a while, and if they stun you, you are dead.  I at 59, fully buffed, I had a quad of Soul Devourers drop me almost 1000 hit points in one shot. (Thank god I had about 2000 at the time)  <br>
<br>
The time you might have gained by quadding is lost in getting a res and getting set back up to fight again.<br>
<br>
My 2 coppers.  <br>
 <p><img src=http://home1.gte.net/chiefq/signamesmall.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usassiful.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sassiful</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/19/01 10:25:46 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.scruz.net/~7thsign/jynx/dragons/images/lance38.jpg hieght=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Qauding At Skyfire</span><hr size=1> Lately I have been kiting in Skyfire and like the room near the zone to BW..as for quad kiting I think you would spend most of your time having to zone to live as its not the most freindly place to play..also I would hate to have to zone and leave 4 mobs to beat on the others playing around the same area.. Causing others deaths due to unlucky kiting because of resists, gives me an uneasy feeling in my stomach.. I am not sure of any other part of Sky to safely quad in as I havent really checked out the whole zone yet.. just my 2c :)<br>
Be safe and well all.<br>
<br>
Sassiful<br>
55 preserver<br>
Prexus <p>-------  Sassiful  -------
