</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uklaymoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>klaymoore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/21/01 8:07:25 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.steelstrip.co.uk/images/KLAYSIZE3.jpg width=120 height=140></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Qauding At Skyfire</span><hr size=1> Agree with two posters above<br>
<br>
Even if do-able its going to be dangerous and deaths can easily counter the exp you may get. If you do decide to try, don't train the BW zone, die where you are. It is so dangerous to others to drop four mobs by the zone. We have a bad enough reputation as it is ! <p><img src="http://www.steelstrip.co.uk/images/klayrf2.gif"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubainwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bainwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/23/01 10:57:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Qauding At Skyfire</span><hr size=1> North of the VP entrance along that wall has some nice flat spots. If you stick to spermies you will be fine, but I wouldnt try it without the Lum staff unless you plan on med kiting.  At 58 with fists it becomes a bit easier.  The hard part is getting 4 spermies, usually best after a patch.  Quadding in skyfire is not for the faint of heart, requires more skill and fast connection.<br>
<br>
Bainwolf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uduad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Duad</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/26/01 11:12:19 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Qauding At Skyfire</span><hr size=1> Agree quad kiting in SF is doable but prob not worth the hassle.  Nice flat spot for hunting in general:  go straight out from the BW zone (over the volcano) to the big lava 'lake' - all along the south edge of that - almost NO wandering mobs - you can kite or root/dot there easily (also can pick up two, sometimes three of the different named cycles from there on tracking). <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=2974.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showMessage?topicID=3061.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.emailToFriend?topicID=3049.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.threadControl?topicID=3049.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3049.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboar